PING : PACKET INTERNET GROPER

    CHECK CONNECTION : ping IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    SEND N PACKETS : ping -c N IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    SEND AT INTERVAL OF N SECONDS : pig -i N IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    SEE ONLY SUMMARY : ping -cN -q IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    SEND PACKET AS FAST AS POSSIBLE : sudo ping -f IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    SEND PACKETS OF N SIZE : ping -s N IPAddress_OR_WebLink 

    STOP AFTER N SECONDS : ping -w N IPAddress_OR_WebLink     

    PRINT WITH TIMESTAMP : ping -D IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    CHECK FOR NETWORK INTERFACE : ping localhost


NETSTAT :

    NUMBER OF CONNECTIONS ON SPECIFIC PORT OR IP : netstat -putan | grep :PortNumber_OR_IPAddress

        p = PID PROGRAM NAME
        u = UDP
        t = TCP
        n = NUMERIC ADDRESS
        l = LISTENING PORT
        a = ALL SOCKETS
        i = INTERFACES

    SEE STATISTICS : netstat -s


TRACE ROUTE : 

    SEE ROUTE : traceroute IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    CHANGE PACKET LENGTH TO N BYTES : traceroute IPAddress_OR_WebLink N

    CHANGE NUMBER OF PACKET PER HOP TO N : traceroute -q N IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    CHECK FOR PORT N : traceroute -p N IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    USE IPV4 OR IPV6 : traceroute -4 OR -6 IPAddress_OR_WebLink

    TRACE THROUGH GATE : traceroute -g Gate_IPAddress IPAddress_OR_WebLink

